fix for this is due in the next few hours
I'm thinking this is still in the queue for fixing - I assume the eCR error we are getting is the same issue? http://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/case-reporting/branches/master/failure/build.log
@Grahame Grieve Still fails in 1.1.39 -- see https://build.fhir.org/ig/HL7/carin-bb/branches/master/failure/build.log

@Grahame Grieve does your fix include a fix for

Outcome of trying to fetch existing package-list,json: Error parsing JSON source: Unexpected char '<' in json stream at Line 1 (path=[null]) Publishing Content Failed: null (00:43.0807) (00:43.0808) Use -? to get command line help (00:43.0808) (00:43.0808) Stack Dump (for debugging): (00:43.0808) java.lang.NullPointerException at org.hl7.fhir.utilities.VersionUtilities.isThisOrLater(VersionUtilities.java:234) at org.hl7.fhir.igtools.renderers.VersionCheckRenderer.generate(VersionCheckRenderer.java:75) at org.hl7.fhir.igtools.publisher.Publisher.createIg(Publisher.java:890) at org.hl7.fhir.igtools.publisher.Publisher.execute(Publisher.java:728) at org.hl7.fhir.igtools.publisher.Publisher.main(Publisher.java:8373)

@Saul Kravitz missed a spot - fixed next release
Thank you. Don't want to be a nag, but the carin-bb folks will ask me when we can republish....so I'm pre-asking you :wink:
My goal is to beat any announcement of winner ;-)
I'm torn regarding which I'm anticipating more: the announcement of 1.1.40 or of the 'winner'.
well, my timeline slipped, but so did the other
We're still getting this error - are we waiting on a fix still (not nagging either... :) )
@Grahame Grieve Could you please shed some light on when the next publisher will be available so we can plan around it? Is it imminent, or should we be counseling our customers for a longer wait?

@Grahame Grieve to be a bit more clear. This is now delaying the vote on the publication of the CARIN IG for BB, which we expected to take up today. Can you give us an estimatation of when this will be fixed? We will need to update CMS to inform them that the final publication of the IG will be delayed until this is fixed.
@Ryan Howells

Sigh. Publishing a new version of UTG has consumed much of my time for the past few days, and I have an unresolved test failure that is holding publication up. My goial is to get a new version today my time
